eRisk2018 is a smaller dataset of {{arxiv_2204_10432_FO0013||FO}} depressed users and {{arxiv_2204_10432_FO0014||FO}} control users curated to evaluate the effectiveness of early risk detection on the Internet. Similar to RSDD, the depression group in eRisk2018 was collected based on user self-reports; Here, posts from mental health subreddits were not excluded like in RSDD. Due to the small size of the original training set, which makes the deep learning approaches unstable, we re-partitioned this dataset to allow more data for training.